NBA ALL-STAR 2020
February 15, 2020
Luka Doncic
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
LUKA DONCIC: I'm just happy to be there on Sunday. It's the All-Star Game. It's the game that it's all about. So I'm really happy to be there.   
 Q.  What stands out to you the most about Chicago?  
LUKA DONCIC: It's really cold. No, but it's a really nice city. I enjoy it. It's a very nice city. So I plan to come back here in the summer when it's a little bit warmer.   
 Q.  On playing in the NBA Rising Stars and hitting a half-court shot:  
LUKA DONCIC: It was amazing. It's the kind of moments I'll remember for the rest of my life. I'm looking forward to more of those moments. It was something just amazing.   
 Q.  Has the Rising Stars game lost some juice?  
LUKA DONCIC: No, not really. It's something special. It's something that I think every kid wants that plays basketball.   
 Q.  What was it like last night with your fellow sophomores, hitting that half-court shot that went viral?  
LUKA DONCIC: It was great. I practiced a lot of those shots. So one of them has got to go in.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT